                content: "Pace is not just about 'Fast' or 'Slow'. It is about **Density** and **Emphasis**. It is about how much information you can transmit *successfully*.\n\nGreat speakers warp time. They can make 5 minutes feel like 1 minute (by being engaging and rhythmic) or make 1 minute feel like an eternity (by using heavy pauses).\n\n**The Transmission Theory:** Communication is not what you say; it is what they *hear*. If you say 500 words and they catch 100, your transmission rate is 20%. If you say 200 words and they catch 180, your transmission rate is 90%. You win with the 90%. Speed without comprehension is just noise.",
