                content: "Statistics are numbing. Stalin famously said (apocryphally): \"One death is a tragedy; a million deaths is a statistic.\"\n\n**The Psychic Numbing Effect:** As the number of victims rises, our empathy flatlines. We cannot care about 1,000,000 people. We can only care about **One Person**.\n\n**The Strategy:** Always anchor your big impacts in a specific Victim. Don't just say \"Poverty rises.\" Say: \"Think of the single mother in Detroit, deciding between buying insulin or buying heat for her apartment. That is the voter.\"\n\n**The Rule:** Zoom In. Make the judge see a face, not a chart.",
                keyPoints: ["Psychic Numbing", "One death = Tragedy", "Zoom In"],
