                type: "content",
                title: "The Warrant: The Bridge",
                content: "The Warrant is the 'Because'. It is the bridge between your Claim and your Data.\n\n*   **Claim:** Minimum wage kills jobs.\n*   **Data:** Card from Cato Institute.\n*   **Warrant (The Logic):** **Because** small businesses operate on thin margins (3-5%). If labor costs rise by 10%, they become mathematically insolvent. They cannot raise prices (competition), so they MUST cut hours.\n\nWithout the Warrant, you just have a Claim. A Claim is air. The Warrant is the steel.\n\n**The Warrant Debate:** Advanced rounds are won on the Warrant level. \"Judge, their Data is fine, but their Warrant (Mechanism) is flawed. History shows businesses absorb costs, they don't fire people.\"",
                keyPoints: ["The 'Because'", "Claim is air", "Warrant is steel"],
                tip: "If you don't know the answer in Cross-Ex, return to the Warrant. 'I don't have the raw data, but the Mechanism is supply and demand...'"
