                content: "Latin for \"Is it not all the more true?\" or \"From the stronger.\"\n\n**The Logic:** If a hard thing is done, an easy thing is guaranteed. If a weak cause produces an effect, a strong cause must produce it too.\n\n**Example:**\n\"If we can't trust the government to fix a Pothole (Easy/Local), how can we possibly trust them to run the entire Healthcare System (Hard/National)?\"\n\nThis is a powerful logical lever. It forces the opponent to defend their competence on the small things first.",
